    "We then prove in Thm.",
    "1 that learning ∇ log p(x s 1:n |x 0 1:n) is equivalent to ∇ log p(x s 1:n |x 0 1:n-1) for θ of M θ in the MSE loss, i.e., their optimal model parameter θ is identical.",
    "At the end, our score network M θ (s, h s n, h 0 n-1) learns ∇ log p(h s n |hn) since RNNs can encode x 0 1:n and x 0 1:n-1 into their hidden states h 0 n and h 0 n-1, respectively.",
